@node "ConfList" "Conference Listview..."
 
 @{b}THE CONFERENCE LISTVIEW@{ub}
 
 At first you`ll see all already installed conferences in this listview as
 marked blue.
 
 Just @{i}double-click@{ui} any conference of the listview, if @{b}dre!week@{ub} is already
 installed in this conference the [@{fg shine}CHANGE@{fg text}|@{fg shine}RESET@{fg text}|@{fg shine}REMOVE@{fg text}] buttons are enabled
 otherwise the [@{fg shine}INSTALL@{fg text}] are enabled.
 Now setup the @{b}dre!week@{ub} data and press install to add @{b}dre!week@{ub} to the sel-
 ected conference, if @{b}dre!week@{ub} is already installed press change to save the
 made changes.
 
 The Listview is features a full cursor-key support, this means you can move
 the cursor bar, by cursor up/down, press return to @{i}double-click@{ui}.
@endnode

@node "HelpText" "HelpText..."
 
 @{b}THE HELP TEXTGADGET@{ub}
 
 This gadget will inform you about the actual modifications and other stuff.
 Not really important, kust usefull to be informed.
@endnode

@node "Install" "Install dre!week data..."
 
 @{b}THE INSTALL BUTTON@{ub}
 
 After you`ve modified the settings for a new conference, you should press
 his button to install the needed files to run @{b}dre!week@{ub} to the selected
 conference path.
@endnode

@node "Change" "Change dre!week data`s"
 
 @{b}THE CHANGE BUTTON@{ub}
 
 After you`ve @{i}double-clicked@{ui} a conference where @{b}dre!week@{ub} is already installed
 modify the settings to your new favorite values and press this button to save
 the new values to the settings of the @{i}selected@{ui} conference.
@endnode

@node "Reset" "Reset dre!week data(s)"
 
 @{b}THE EDIT BUTTON@{ub}
 
 After @{i}double-click@{ui} a conference where @{b}dre!week@{ub} is already installed, you can
 reset the @{b}dre!week@{ub} data`s manually for a new period, press this button,
 the preferences program will now clear the database, after this it will ask you
 to reset the top uploaders also, select @{b}no@{ub} to @{b}keep@{ub} the existing top uploader of
 the last period and for all time.
@endnode

@node "Remove" "Remove dre!week data(s)"
 
 @{b}THE REMOVE BUTTON@{ub}
 
 @{i}Double-click@{ui} the conference of the listview where you wish to @{u}remove@{uu} @{b}dre!week@{ub}
 from. Press this button and this preferences program will @{i}remove@{ui} the datafile
 from the choosen conference.
 
 @{b}Be carefull, you can`t get back removed datafiles !!!@{ub}
@endnode

@node "WriteMessage" "Write Message Switch"
 
 @{b}WRITE MESSAGE SWITCH@{ub}
 
 Here you can toggle the message function on/off. Set this button to true, if
 you want to post a message after each period to the conference msgbase.
@endnode

@node "AnsiMessage" "ANSI Message switch"
 
 @{b}ANSI MESSAGE SWITCH@{ub}
 
 Switch this button to true, if you like to post a message with ANSI colors
 after each timer interval.
 
 @{b}@{u}NOTE:@{ub}@{uu} This button is useless if you have the @{"write message" link "WriteMessage" 0} button switched
       off.
@endnode

@node "ShowLogo" "Show header switch..."
 
 @{b}THE SHOW LOGO SWITCH@{ub}
 
 Here you can toggle the show-logo (header) option. Set this to true, to
 display the header defined in the @{"Header" link "Header" 0} string-gadget.
 
 @{b}@{u}NOTE:@{ub}@{uu} If you set this to true and you hav`nt defined a header, @{b}dre!week@{ub} will
       make @{u}automatic a screen-clear.@{uu}
@endnode

@node "ShowRecords" "Show records switch..."
 
 @{b}THE SHOW RECORDS SWITCH@{ub}
 
 Here you can toggle the record display fucntion, set it to false and you`ll
 see just the weektop uploader, enable it to see also the top uploader of all
 time and the last period.
@endnode

@node "NoSysop" "No Sysop uloads switch..."
 
 @{b}THE NO SYSOP SWITCH@{ub}
 
 Set this button on to skip all sysop uploads. Otherwise all sysop uploads are
 added to the weektop database.
@endnode

@node "Rows" "Number of Users to display..."
 
 @{b}THE USER SLIDER@{ub}
 
 Here you can define the number of users shown in the output.
 @{fg fill}iE. Set it to 12 to list the 12 top uploader of the week.@{fg text}
 
 @{b}Default and mininum amount are 10 users !!!@{ub}
@endnode

@node "Period" "Number of Day`s (Period)..."
 
 @{b}THE DAY SLIDER@{ub}
 
 Specify here the time period in days. After this period the database will be
 cleared and if @{"write message" link "WriteMessage" 0} is enabled a message about the result of the
 last period posted to the message base.
  
@{fg shine} Default days are 7@{fg text}

 @{fg shine}Maximum days are 365 - if one needs more contact me.@{fg text}
@endnode

@node "MSGStat" "Status of the Message"
 
 @{b}THE MESSAGE STATUS CYCLEBAR@{ub}
 
 Here you can switch between "@{b}@{fg shine}EALL@{ub}@{fg text}" and "@{b}@{fg shine}AL@{ub}@{fg text}L" for the message status.
 
 @{b}@{u}NOTE:@{ub}@{uu} If write message is disabled this gadget is totally useless.
 
 Default is "@{b}@{fg fill}EALL@{ub}@{fg text}"
@endnode

@node "MinBytes" "Amount of min. bytes..."
 
 @{b}THE MIN BYTES INTEGER@{ub}
 
 Specify here the minimum amount of bytes a user must upload to get added to
@{b} dre!week`s@{ub} database.
 All uploads with lower byte amount are skipped.
 
 Default is "@{b}@{fg fill}0@{ub}@{fg text}"
@endnode

@node "Header" "Enter Header path to diplay..."
 
 @{b}THE HEADER STRINGGADGET@{ub}
 
 Here you can enter the @{b}full path@{ub} to your external headerfile, to displayed
 above the weektop output.
 
 @{b}@{u}NOTE:@{ub}@{uu} This is useless if the the @{"show logo" link "ShowLogo" 0} button is switched off.
@endnode

@node "GetHeader" "Get the Header via reqtools-requester..."
 
 @{b}THE GETHEADERFILE BUTTON@{ub}
 
 Press this small (@{fg shine}nice@{fg text}) popfile-button to activate a reqtools requester to
 select the path of the external headerfile via the requester.
 
 @{b}@{u}NOTE:@{ub}@{uu} This totally useless if the show logo button is switched off !!!
@endnode

@node "Features" "Features..."
 
 @{b}THE FEATURES OF DRE!WEEK v2.0@{ub}
 
 + Preferences GUI
 + Very, very fast sort algorythm
 - Own headerfile defineable
 + defineable output
 + Message posting
 ? free defineable time periods        (@{b}@{fg shine}PUBLIC VERSION max. 7 Days@{ub}@{fg text})
 ? User output amount of max. 30 users (@{b}@{fg shine}PUBLIC VERSION max. 10 Users@{ub}@{fg text})
 + Full amigaguide helpkey support
 + ansi/nonansi message output
 - skip sysop u/l defineable
 - keep`s records of all time and the last period
 + Save byte function
 + and even many more nice features

 @{b}@{u}NOTE:@{ub}@{uu} @{b}Some all options marked with a '-' are only for the registered users!
 All options marked with a '?' are limited to control!@{ub}
@endnode

@node "Installation" "Installation..."
 
 THE INSTALLATION
 
 dRE!WEEk supports the amiga standard installation program. 
 Just double-click the install icon of your preferred language and follow
 the installer instrcutions.
 
 @{b}I`ve spend a lot of time to write the install script, so I`m to tired to write
 the manual installation !!!@{ub}
@endnode

