@node "dRE!WEEk" "dRE!WEEk (DOOR)..."
 
 @{b}HOW TO USE DRE!WEEK (DOOR)@{ub}
 
 There is nothing to use, just build the Weektop via the MCI Commands in your
 BULL.txt(.gr) in all conferences where you have @{b}dre!week@{ub} installed, like this
 small example:
 
 ---------------------------[@{b}@{fg fill}SNIP HERE@{ub}@{fg text}]--------------------------
 ~
 ~CC_WEEKTOP 
 ---------------------------[@{b}@{fg fill}SNIP HERE@{ub}@{fg text}]--------------------------

 @{b}@{fg shine}NOTE THE SPACE AFTER EACH MCI COMMAND@{ub}@{fg text}
@endnode

@node "dRE!WEEk-GUI" "dRE!WEEk-preferences (GUI)..."
 
 @{b}HOW TO USE THE DRE!WEEK PREFRENCES PROGRAM@{ub}
 
  @{b}THIS GUI SUPPORTS THE AMIGAGUIDE HELP, VIA THE HELPKEY, THIS MEANS YOU CAN
    MOVE YOUR MOUSE ABOVE ANY GADGET OR MENUITEM AND LAUNCH THE AMIGAGUIDE 
              WITH THE CORRECT NODE BY PRESSING YOUR HELP-KEY@{ub}


 @{b}@{fg shine}INSTALL DRE!WEEK TO A CONFERENCE@{ub}@{fg text}
 @{b}--------------------------------@{ub}
 Just double-click it`s icon to popup the GUI. No you`ll see a list of all your
 in FAME installed conferences. Double-click the conferences where you wish
 to install dre!week. The Install button will be enabled, set now up your
 prefered values for the weektop output and press the @{"install" link "Install" 0} button.
 If all was okay, the installed conferences will now shown colored.
 
 @{b}@{fg shine}CHANGE VALUES OF AN ALREADY INSTALLED CONFERENCE@{ub}@{fg text}
 @{b}------------------------------------------------@{ub}
 To change the values of a already installed conference, just double-click
 the conference and the change/reset/remove buttons are enabled, set now the
 new parametes and press @{"change" link "Change" 0} to keep it.

 @{b}@{fg shine}RESET DRE!WEEK OF AN ALREADY INSTALLED CONFERENCE@{ub}@{fg text}
 @{b}-------------------------------------------------@{ub}
 Choose a conference via double-click of the conf-listview and press the @{"reset" link "Reset" 0}
 button, all values are now cleared, a requester wil popup and ask you if you
 wish to reset the topuploader too.

 @{b}@{fg shine}REMOVE DRE!WEEK FROM A CHHOOSEN CONFERENCE@{ub}@{fg text}
 @{b}------------------------------------------@{ub}
 Choose a conference via double-click and press the @{"remove" link "Remove" 0} button.
 The Preferences program will remove dre!week from this conference.
@endnode

